    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-basa-and-black-olive-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 5 min until softened but not coloured</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-basa-and-black-olive-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-basa-and-black-olive-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>arborio rice</strong> and <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) to the pan, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-basa-and-black-olive-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add them to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-basa-and-black-olive-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and place them on the same tray[s]</p><p>Drizzle everything with<strong> olive oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Season the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> with a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min until the fish is cooked</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Do this in batches!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-basa-and-black-olive-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> capers</strong> and <strong>black olives</strong> together finely</p><p>Combine both with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tapenade</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-basa-and-black-olive-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, remove it from the heat and stir in a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, the <strong>roasted cherry tomatoes </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>tapenade</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>black olive risotto</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> baked basa</strong> over the <strong>black olive</strong> <strong>risotto</strong> with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>tapenade</strong> spooned over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
